Kwanza, matokeo haya yameorodheshwa katika Zoo ya Ugumu: https://complexityzoo.uwaterloo.ca/complexity_zoo:n#npiconp. Vinginevyo, inawezekana kudhibitisha bila shida sana (ambayo mimi hufanya chini). Tunataka kuonyesha kuwa $ p^{np \ cap conp} = np \ cap conp $. Kwa wazi, mwelekeo mmoja ni kweli: $ np \ cap conp \ subseteq p^{np \ cap conp} $. Ili kudhibitisha mwelekeo mwingine, inatosha kuonyesha kuwa $ p^{np \ cap conp} \ subseteq np $ tangu wakati huo $ p^{np \ cap conp} \ subseteq conp $ ifuatavyo kwa kukamilisha lugha zote zinazohusika na kama matokeo $ p^{np \ cap conp} \ subseteq np \ cap conp $. Basi wacha tuthibitishe kuwa $ p^{np \ cap conp} \ subseteq np $. Tuseme kuwa tunayo mashine ya kuamua ya wakati wa polynomial $ m $ ambayo hufanya maswali ya Oracle kwa lugha katika $ np \ cap conp $. Tunafafanua mashine mpya, isiyo ya kuamua $ M '$ kulingana na $ M $ kama ifuatavyo: kuiga $ M $ hadi $ M $ inahitaji kuendesha swala la Oracle kwenye pembejeo fulani $ X $ kwa lugha fulani $ L $. Katika hatua hiyo, endesha subroutine ambayo matawi ya $ m '$ katika idadi fulani ya matawi ambayo kila moja inajaribu kujifunza jibu la swala la Oracle. Subroutine imeundwa ili hakuna tawi litajifunza jibu lisilofaa, angalau tawi moja hujifunza jibu sahihi, na matawi kadhaa hupata "kutofautisha" kama matokeo wakati wa kujaribu kujifunza jibu la swala. Katika $ m '$, matawi yaliyo na matokeo yasiyofaa kisha yanakataa. Katika hatua hii, matawi pekee yaliyobaki ni yale ambayo yanajua jibu sahihi kwa swala. Kwa hivyo tunaweza kuendelea na simulation ya $ m $ katika matawi haya. Katika the end of the simulation, the only branches which haven't rejected are the ones which successfully got through all of the steps of the simulation. These branches accept iff $M$ accepts, so the overall $NP$   Since $L \in NP \cap coNP$, there exists a NP machine $N_L$ with language $L$ and another machine $N_{
eg L}$ whose language is the complement of $L$. To simulate the oracle query (is $x$ in $L$), $M'$ first runs $N_L$ on $x$ and then runs $N_{
eg L}$ on $x$ in every branch. Every resulting branch will have one branch of $N_L$'s computation and one branch of $N_{
eg L}$'s computation. Within any single branch, both the $N_L$ computaion and the $N_{
eg L}$ computation cannot be accepting since that would require $x$ to both be in $L$ and in $
eg L$. Thus each branch will have either the $N_L$ computation accepting, the $N_{
eg L}$ computation accepting, or neither computation accepting. Furthermore, there must be at least one accepting branch of either $N_L$ or $N_{
eg L}$. Next, $M'$ rejects in the branches in which the computations of both $N_L$ and $N_{
eg L}$ reject. In all other branches, $M'$ has learned the answer to the oracle query (since either $N_L$ or $N_{
eg L}$ accept $x$ in the particular branch considered in this $M'$ branch). At that point, $M'$ can continue the simulation of $M$. Note that the simulation will actually continue in at least one branch since at least one accepting branch of either $N_L$ or $N_{
eg L}$ exits.
